Do you not think that the virtue os him who⁴ bravely storms the enemy’s stronghold is equal to that of him who endures a siege with the utmost patience? Great is Scipio when he invests Numantia? and constrains and compels the hands of an enemy, whom he could not conquer‚ to resort to their own destruction. Great also are the souls of the defenders——men who know that, as long as the path to death lies open, the blockade is not complete, men who breathe their last in the arms of liberty. In like manner, the other virtues are also equal as compared with one another: tranquillity‚ simplicity, generosity, con- stancy, equanimity, endurance.
